OL,3,CComet passing by once every 71 years
OL,4,Cnow visible in night sky
OL,6,FA comet that passes by Earth once
OL,7,Fevery 71 years is currently visible in
OL,8,Fthe night sky using binoculars or
OL,9,Fsmall telescopes.
OL,11,FAstronomers say 12P/Pons-Brooks is
OL,12,Fgrowing brighter and there is a
OL,13,Fpossibility sky gazers will be able to
OL,14,Fsee it with the naked eye in the
OL,15,Fcoming weeks.
OL,17,FIt has already had several outbursts
OL,18,Fof activity, raising its brightness
OL,19,Fperiodically, according to Dr Megan
OL,20,FArgo, an astrophysicist at the
OL,21,FUniversity of Central Lancashire.
