OL,4,Cnow visible in night sky
OL,6,FShe added: "If we're lucky, it may
OL,7,Fhave another in the next few weeks as
OL,8,Fit passes through the sky."
OL,10,FComets are celestial objects mainly
OL,11,Fmade up of dust, rock and ice.
OL,13,FDr Argo said: "You can think of them
OL,14,Fas a bit like giant dirty snowballs."
OL,16,F12P/Pons-Brooks, named after its
OL,17,Fdiscoverers Jean-Louis Pons and
OL,18,FWilliam Robert Brooks, spends most of
OL,19,Fits time in the outer reaches of the
OL,20,FSolar System, where it is very cold.
