OL,3,CComet passing by once every 71 years
OL,4,Cnow visible in night sky
OL,6,FIt comes back to the inner Solar
OL,7,FSystem every 71 years and is, hence,
OL,8,Fknown as a periodic comet.
OL,10,FDr Argo said that as the comet gets
OL,11,Fclose to the Sun, the heat causes the
OL,12,Fice to melt straight to gas ` through
OL,13,Fa process called sublimation ` and
OL,14,Fsome of the material is lost from the
OL,15,Fsurface.
OL,17,FShe said: "This gas forms both a cloud
OL,18,Faround the solid nucleus of the comet
OL,19,F` known as the coma ` and a tail of
OL,20,Fmaterial that can stretch many
OL,21,Fmillions of miles in space.
