OL,3,CComet passing by once every 71 years
OL,4,Cnow visible in night sky
OL,6,F"The tail is made of gas and dust that
OL,7,Fhas been pushed away from the comet by
OL,8,Fthe power of the solar wind streaming
OL,9,Ffrom the Sun, and this tail is the bit
OL,10,Fthat can become spectacular in the sky
OL,11,Fas seen from Earth."
OL,13,FDr Argo said that while 12P/Pons-
OL,14,FBrooks is developing a nice tail, it
OL,15,Fis "not quite visible without
OL,16,Fbinoculars or a telescope just yet".
OL,18,FFor those looking to spot the comet,
OL,19,Fit is below ` and slightly to the left
OL,20,F` of the Andromeda galaxy.
