OL,3,CComet passing by once every 71 years
OL,4,Cnow visible in night sky
OL,6,FMr Atkinson, who has written 14 books
OL,7,Fon astronomy, said: "Over the next few
OL,8,Fweek or so it will brighten a little
OL,9,Fmore, but the Moon is in the sky now,
OL,10,Fand its brightness will dim the comet."
OL,12,FHe said the best way to see the comet
OL,13,Fis to find a place with dark skies and
OL,14,Fno tall trees, buildings or hills to
OL,15,Fblock the views.
OL,17,FHe said: "You'll need binoculars to
OL,18,Fsee the comet, and even then it will
OL,19,Fonly look like a smudgy star with a
OL,20,Fhint of a tail behind it.
OL,26,@oD@UOUrD@gO]yD@JOU
