PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F303A1710665352
OL,3,CComet passing by once every 71 years
OL,4,Cnow visible in night sky
OL,6,F"Luckily there's a bright planet quite
OL,7,Fclose to it ` Jupiter ` so if you pan
OL,8,Fyour binoculars to the right of
OL,9,FJupiter, very slowly, that will help.
OL,11,F"People think comets whoosh across the
OL,12,Fsky, like shooting stars, but that's
OL,13,Fnot true, they only move a small
OL,14,Famount each night, so the comet will
OL,15,Fbe in the sky for a while yet."
OL,17,FFor those wanting to take photos, Mr
OL,18,FAtkinson advises using a DSLR camera
OL,19,Fon a tripod or a telescope.
